summary: Anne Paul Wilander was an employee of the Select Committee on Assassinations (SCA). The documents available are certification reports detailing payroll information. These reports list her name, social security number, position, salary, and employment dates. She was employed by the committee at least from August 1978 to January 1979.
significance: Anne Paul Wilander's significance lies in her employment with the Select Committee on Assassinations, indicating her involvement in the investigation of the JFK assassination, although the specific nature or extent of her role is not detailed in these documents.
